messages.content:
Certainly! Below is a simple implementation of an ELIZA-like chatbot in a single HTML file. This code includes embedded CSS for styling and JavaScript for functionality. You can copy and paste this code into an HTML file and open it in a web browser to see it in action.

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>ELIZA Chatbot</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            background-color: #f4f4f4;
            margin: 0;
            padding: 20px;
        }
        #chatbox {
            width: 100%;
            max-width: 600px;
            margin: 0 auto;
            background: white;
            border-radius: 5px;
            box-shadow: 0 0 10px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
            padding: 20px;
        }
        #messages {
            height: 300px;
            overflow-y: auto;
            border: 1px solid #ccc;
            padding: 10px;
            margin-bottom: 10px;
            border-radius: 5px;
            background: #fafafa;
        }
        #userInput {
            width: calc(100% - 22px);
            padding: 10px;
            border: 1px solid #ccc;
            border-radius: 5px;
        }
        #sendButton {
            padding: 10px 15px;
            background: #007BFF;
            color: white;
            border: none;
            border-radius: 5px;
            cursor: pointer;
        }
        #sendButton:hover {
            background: #0056b3;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>

<div id="chatbox">
    <h2>ELIZA Chatbot</h2>
    <div id="messages"></div>
    <input type="text" id="userInput" placeholder="Type your message here..." />
    <button id="sendButton">Send</button>
</div>

<script>
    const responses = {
        "hello": "Hello! How can I help you today?",
        "how are you": "I'm just a computer program, but thanks for asking!",
        "what is your name": "I am ELIZA, your virtual therapist.",
        "bye": "Goodbye! Take care.",
        "default": "Tell me more about that."
    };

    function getResponse(userInput) {
        const lowerInput = userInput.toLowerCase();
        return responses[lowerInput] || responses["default"];
    }

    function addMessage(sender, message) {
        const messagesDiv = document.getElementById("messages");
        messagesDiv.innerHTML += `<strong>${sender}:</strong> ${message}<br>`;
        messagesDiv.scrollTop = messagesDiv.scrollHeight; // Scroll to the bottom
    }

    document.getElementById("sendButton").addEventListener("click", function() {
        const userInput = document.getElementById("userInput").value;
        if (userInput.trim() === "") return;

        addMessage("You", userInput);
        const botResponse = getResponse(userInput);
        addMessage("ELIZA", botResponse);
        document.getElementById("userInput").value = ""; // Clear input
    });

    document.getElementById("userInput").addEventListener("keypress", function(event) {
        if (event.key === "Enter") {
            document.getElementById("sendButton").click();
        }
    });
</script>

</body>
</html>
```

### How to Use:
1. Copy the code above.
2. Paste it into a text editor and save it as `eliza.html`.
3. Open the `eliza.html` file in a web browser.

You can then interact with the ELIZA chatbot by typing messages into the input box and clicking the "Send" button or pressing the "Enter" key. The bot will respond based on predefined responses. You can expand the `responses` object in the JavaScript section to add more phrases and responses.
